<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bpmn:definitions xmlns:bpmn="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL"
                  xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI"
                  xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC"
                  xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI"
                  id="Definitions_NcrCapaLoop" targetNamespace="http://bpmn.io/schema/bpmn">
  <bpmn:collaboration id="Collaboration_NcrCapaLoop">
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_NcrCapaLoop" name="Edge Case e04 - Nonconformance to CAPA to Supplier Re-evaluation Loop" processRef="Process_NcrCapaLoop" />
  </bpmn:collaboration>
  <bpmn:process id="Process_NcrCapaLoop" isExecutable="false">
    <bpmn:laneSet id="LaneSet_NcrCapaLoop">
      <bpmn:lane id="L_recv" name="Receiving / Warehouse">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Start</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_qc" name="Quality">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Inspect</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwConform</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>RaiseNcr</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwDisposition</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Effectiveness</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwEffective</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_buyer" name="Procurement / Buyer">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Scar</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_supplier" name="Supplier / Vendor">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>RootCause</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_sys" name="Platform / System">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Release</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>ReturnPath</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>ReworkScrap</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>ReEval</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwSuspend</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Suspend</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Monitor</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>End</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
    </bpmn:laneSet>
    <bpmn:startEvent id="Start" name="Goods received for inspection">
      <bpmn:documentation>Entry. Goods are received against the requisition/PO and presented for receiving verification. This edge case isolates the ISO feedback loop 8.6 -&gt; 8.7 -&gt; 10.2 -&gt; 8.4.1. [SCOR S2.5 Inspect and Verify | ISO 8.6 release/receiving verification | source: albahja-receiving-inspection-grn + iso-supply-chain-standards central feedback loop]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f1</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:startEvent>
    <bpmn:userTask id="Inspect" name="8.6 Receiving inspection / verification">
      <bpmn:documentation>Quality performs receiving verification (qc.inspect). Materials path: store sends COA + sample to QC; QC inspects/tests against spec (skip-lot / sampling / 100% / source inspection / CoC-only per the risk-based inspection level set by ISO 8.4.2 item criticality). Hard block: no COA -&gt; cannot release (AB rule). Retain conformity evidence + traceability to the authorizing person (ISO 8.6). Spares/services bypass QC (received by Engineering against the requisition, no GRN) - an NCR there is raised by Engineering. [SCOR S2.5 | ISO 8.6 | source: albahja-receiving-inspection-grn + iso 8.4.2/8.6]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f1</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f2</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:userTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwConform" name="conforming?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Gate. QC result == pass (within spec, COA valid, quantity within PO tolerance) -&gt; conforming: release, GRN raised, GR/IR accrued, onward to invoicing (diagram 08/09); no NCR. QC result == fail / quarantine (off-spec, damage, missing/invalid COA, expired, wrong item) -&gt; nonconforming: raise NCR. NCRs can also be raised AFTER GRN when QC finds damage/off-spec later (post-GRN NCR re-enters here). [SCOR S2.5 | ISO 8.6/8.7 | source: albahja-receiving-inspection-grn QC approved? + post-GRN NCR]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f2</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f3</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f4</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="Release" name="Release - GRN raised (no NCR)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Conforming outcome. GRN raised (links requisition + PO reference), GR/IR liability accrued, commitment relieved to actual (e02), delivery counts toward OTD/OTIF and the four-factor perfect-order metric (diagram 12). Quantity tolerance: labels/cartons/printed packaging routinely +/-5-10% from ordered -&gt; handler adjusts PO qty to actual before GRN (audited); no-tolerance items skip adjustment. This branch terminates the loop with no nonconformance. [SCOR S2.6 | ISO 8.6 | source: albahja-receiving-inspection-grn GRN + e02 relief]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f3</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f5</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:userTask id="RaiseNcr" name="8.7 Raise NCR (identify + segregate)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Raise the NCR (ncr.raise). Fields (AB + ISO 8.7): item (name/itemId), deliveryNote# (mandatory), date (delivery date), description of non-compliance (mandatory), percentNonConformance (0-100), image (&gt;=1 attachment). raisedBy = QC, Finance-Maker (C: FM raise), or requester / Engineering (C: eng raise). Goods are physically identified and SEGREGATED (quarantine bin) per ISO 8.7 so nonconforming product cannot be used unintentionally. NCR status = raised; SSE + audit (category: ticket/quality). [SCOR S2.5 | ISO 8.7 control of nonconforming outputs | source: albahja-receiving-inspection-grn NCR fields + iso 8.7 identify/segregate]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f4</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f6</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:userTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwDisposition" name="disposition?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Disposition decision (ISO 8.7 correction/return/concession). Exact set: {return | rework | use-as-is-concession | scrap}. return -&gt; hands to the RMA flow (diagram 11, S4) with linkedNcrId set. rework -&gt; supplier or in-house correction then re-inspect. use-as-is-concession -&gt; accept off-spec under a documented concession (deciding authority recorded). scrap -&gt; write off (no return, debit note may be raised). The deciding authority and the disposition are retained on the NCR (ISO 8.7 record requirement). All four dispositions still proceed to SCAR/CAPA when the cause is systemic. [SCOR S2.5 | ISO 8.7 | source: data-model disposition {return|rework|use-as-is-concession|scrap} + iso 8.7]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f6</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f7</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f8</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="ReturnPath" name="Return -&gt; RMA (diagram 11)">
      <bpmn:documentation>disposition == return: control passes to the Returns/RMA flow (diagram 11, SCOR S4.1-S4.5) carrying linkedNcrId. The physical return (authorize -&gt; identify condition -&gt; schedule shipment -&gt; close/adjust with credit/debit note) runs there; this loop continues in parallel with the systemic CAPA. [SCOR S4 | ISO 8.7 | source: data-model NCR/Return loop + diagram 11 cross-link]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f7</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f9</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="ReworkScrap" name="Rework / concession / scrap (retain record)">
      <bpmn:documentation>disposition IN {rework, use-as-is-concession, scrap}: rework -&gt; correction + re-inspection (loops to 8.6 on re-presentation); use-as-is-concession -&gt; documented acceptance, concession authority retained, supplier may issue a credit for the concession discount; scrap -&gt; write-off, buyer may raise a debit note for the scrapped value. Each retains the ISO 8.7 record (nature, action taken, concession, deciding authority). [ISO 8.7 | source: iso 8.7 disposition records + data-model credit/debit note]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f8</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f10</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:userTask id="Scar" name="Handler resolves with supplier (SCAR)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Procurement handler (capa.manage, with supplier) issues a Supplier Corrective Action Request (SCAR) for any systemic nonconformance. The handler resolves with the supplier: replace / credit / corrective action. The SCAR opens the CAPA record {ncrId, supplierId, ...} and sets a response SLA. CAPA responsiveness (avg days to close) feeds the scorecard responsiveness dimension. [ISO 10.2 / 8.4 | source: albahja-receiving-inspection-grn handler resolves with supplier + role-permission-matrix capa.manage]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f9</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f10</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f14</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f11</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:userTask>
    <bpmn:userTask id="RootCause" name="10.2 Supplier root cause + corrective action">
      <bpmn:documentation>Supplier (capa.manage C: respond) submits the corrective action via the external form (email + OTP): rootCause (mandatory, e.g. 5-why), correctiveAction (immediate correction), preventiveAction (systemic, prevent recurrence), targetDate, evidence attachments. CAPA status = action-proposed. ISO 10.2 requires root cause, action, and a later effectiveness review, all retained. [ISO 10.2 nonconformity and corrective action | source: data-model CorrectiveAction/CAPA rootCause/action + iso 10.2]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f11</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f12</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:userTask>
    <bpmn:userTask id="Effectiveness" name="Effectiveness review">
      <bpmn:documentation>Quality reviews effectiveness (capa.manage): verify the corrective action actually prevented recurrence (e.g. next N lots conforming, no repeat NCR within a window). effectivenessReview field {pending | effective | not-effective}. not-effective -&gt; re-open the SCAR (loop back to root cause). effective -&gt; CAPA closed, NCR closed (NCR closes when disposition done AND, if CAPA opened, effectiveness verified). [ISO 10.2 effectiveness review | source: data-model effectivenessReview + iso 10.2]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f12</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f13</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:userTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwEffective" name="effective?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Gate. effectivenessReview == 'effective' -&gt; close CAPA + NCR, feed re-evaluation. effectivenessReview == 'not-effective' -&gt; re-open SCAR, supplier resubmits root cause/action (loop). Repeated not-effective outcomes contribute to the consecutive-below counter and weigh toward suspension. [ISO 10.2 | source: data-model NCR closed when effectiveness verified]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f13</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f14</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f15</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="ReEval" name="8.4.1 Feed supplier re-evaluation (scorecard)">
      <bpmn:documentation>The closed NCR/CAPA feeds supplier monitoring + re-evaluation (ISO 8.4.1). The NCR counts against the quality dimension (PPM/defect/NCR rate) and, if late/wrong/damaged, against the four-factor perfect-order RL.1.2; CAPA responsiveness feeds the responsiveness dimension; recurring NCRs auto-affect the composite (the platform CHAINS 8.6-&gt;8.7-&gt;10.2-&gt;8.4.1 so the score reflects the loop). Re-computes the period scorecard (diagram 12) and updates the consecutive-below streak counter. [ISO 8.4.1 monitoring/re-evaluation | source: iso central feedback loop 'recurring NCRs auto-affect supplier score' + diagram 12]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f15</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f16</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwSuspend" name="suspend supplier?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Suspend gate (event-driven, ISO 8.4.1 re-evaluation -&gt; AVL status). Trigger conditions (configurable): a critical NCR, two consecutive periods below target (consecutive-below counter), a failed audit, an expired mandatory ISO cert, a sanctions hit, or an unresolved/not-effective active CAPA. If any trigger holds -&gt; set supplier ONBOARDED -&gt; SUSPENDED (blocks new POs without offboarding). Suspend is split by permission: Quality (suppliers.suspend C: quality stop), Tax/Compliance (C: compliance/sanctions hit), Admin (always). Else -&gt; remain ONBOARDED, monitoring continues. [ISO 8.4.1 | source: data-model supplier SUSPENDED state + role-permission-matrix split suspend + iso event triggers]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f16</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f17</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f18</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="Suspend" name="Suspend supplier (SUSPENDED, block new POs)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Set supplier.status = SUSPENDED with suspendReason + suspendedBy + suspendedAt. SUSPENDED blocks new PO issue (PO guard requires supplier ONBOARDED) but does not offboard; existing open POs are handled per policy. AVL status set to Suspended (diagram 12). On resolution (effective CAPA, renewed cert, lifted sanction) SUSPENDED -&gt; ONBOARDED. Notifications to buyer, QC, management; audit logged. [ISO 8.4.1 | source: data-model 'ONBOARDED -&gt; SUSPENDED ... SUSPENDED blocks new POs; SUSPENDED -&gt; ONBOARDED on resolution']</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f17</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f19</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="Monitor" name="Continue monitoring (remain ONBOARDED)">
      <bpmn:documentation>No suspend trigger met. Supplier remains ONBOARDED; the scorecard, streak counters, and risk-based re-evaluation cadence (monthly KPI / quarterly review / annual re-approval, sooner for critical/high-risk) continue. The closed NCR/CAPA stays on the supplier's corrective-action log. [ISO 8.4.1 | source: iso re-eval cadence + data-model monitoring]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f18</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f20</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:endEvent id="End" name="NCR/CAPA closed, supplier re-evaluated">
      <bpmn:documentation>Terminal. NCR dispositioned + (if systemic) CAPA closed with verified effectiveness; supplier re-evaluated; AVL status updated; supplier suspended or continuing under monitoring. The full ISO 8.6 -&gt; 8.7 -&gt; 10.2 -&gt; 8.4.1 loop is closed and recorded. [ISO 8.6-&gt;8.7-&gt;10.2-&gt;8.4.1 / SCOR OE3 | source: build-new + iso loop]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f5</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f19</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f20</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f1" sourceRef="Start" targetRef="Inspect" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f2" sourceRef="Inspect" targetRef="GwConform" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f3" name="conforming (pass)" sourceRef="GwConform" targetRef="Release" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f4" name="nonconforming (fail / quarantine / post-GRN)" sourceRef="GwConform" targetRef="RaiseNcr" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f5" sourceRef="Release" targetRef="End" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f6" sourceRef="RaiseNcr" targetRef="GwDisposition" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f7" name="return" sourceRef="GwDisposition" targetRef="ReturnPath" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f8" name="rework / concession / scrap" sourceRef="GwDisposition" targetRef="ReworkScrap" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f9" sourceRef="ReturnPath" targetRef="Scar" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f10" sourceRef="ReworkScrap" targetRef="Scar" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f11" sourceRef="Scar" targetRef="RootCause" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f12" sourceRef="RootCause" targetRef="Effectiveness" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f13" sourceRef="Effectiveness" targetRef="GwEffective" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f14" name="not-effective (re-open SCAR)" sourceRef="GwEffective" targetRef="Scar" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f15" name="effective (close CAPA + NCR)" sourceRef="GwEffective" targetRef="ReEval" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f16" sourceRef="ReEval" targetRef="GwSuspend" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f17" name="critical NCR / 2 consecutive below / failed audit / expired cert / sanctions / active CAPA" sourceRef="GwSuspend" targetRef="Suspend" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f18" name="no trigger - continue" sourceRef="GwSuspend" targetRef="Monitor" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f19" sourceRef="Suspend" targetRef="End" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f20" sourceRef="Monitor" targetRef="End" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="NoteNcrCapa">
      <bpmn:text>The ISO feedback loop 8.6 -&gt; 8.7 -&gt; 10.2 -&gt; 8.4.1, chained so recurring NCRs auto-affect the supplier score. Receiving inspection (8.6, COA hard block) detects nonconforming -&gt; raise NCR (8.7: item, delivery-note#, date, description, %non-conformance, image; raised by QC/FM/requester; goods segregated) -&gt; disposition {return|rework|use-as-is-concession|scrap} -&gt; handler resolves with supplier via SCAR -&gt; supplier root-cause + corrective action (10.2) -&gt; effectiveness review (not-effective re-opens the SCAR) -&gt; feeds supplier scorecard re-evaluation (8.4.1) -&gt; suspend gate: critical NCR / two consecutive periods below target / failed audit / expired cert / sanctions / active CAPA -&gt; SUSPENDED (blocks new POs), else continue monitoring. Suspend is split: Quality on a quality stop, Tax/Compliance on sanctions, Admin always.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Assoc_NcrCapaLoop_1" sourceRef="ReEval" targetRef="NoteNcrCapa" />
  </bpmn:process>
  <bpmndi:BPMNDiagram id="Diagram_NcrCapaLoop">
    <bpmndi:BPMNPlane id="Plane_NcrCapaLoop" bpmnElement="Collaboration_NcrCapaLoop">
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="Participant_NcrCapaLoop_di" bpmnElement="Participant_NcrCapaLoop" isHorizontal="true">
        <dc:Bounds x="160" y="80" width="2920" height="800" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="L_recv_di" bpmnElement="L_recv" isHorizontal="true">
        <dc:Bounds x="190" y="80" width="2890" height="160" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="L_qc_di" bpmnElement="L_qc" isHorizontal="true">
        <dc:Bounds x="190" y="240" width="2890" height="160" />
